    tool_output=ToolOutput(
        output="Based on the provided text chunks, here is a detailed description of the **AI segment (xAI)**, including its revenue drivers, customer metrics, KPIs, cost structure, and forward-looking information.\n\n---\n\n### **Segment Description**\nThe AI segment operates a **highly vertically integrated AI platform** encompassing:\n*   **Gigawatt-scale AI compute infrastructure** (e.g., the COLOSSUS II Facility in Memphis, Tennessee).\n*   **Grok**, the company's truth-seeking frontier AI model.\n*   **AI solutions** for consumer and enterprise customers.\n*   **X**, the real-time information, entertainment, and free speech platform.\n\nThe company's strategic view is that AI is rapidly converging toward **Artificial General Intelligence (AGI)**, which will require vast, cost-efficient computational resources for broad deployment. Therefore, building large-scale, power-efficient infrastructure is a **critical strategic differentiator**.\n\n### **Revenue Drivers & Sources**\nThe AI segment generates revenue from digital platform services, broken down as follows:\n\n1.  **Advertising:**\n    *   Revenue from ad products displayed on the **X platform**.\n    *   Recognized when a user engages with an ad in a manner satisfying the advertiser's criteria.\n    *   Subject to seasonality, with highest spend in Q4 and lowest in Q1.\n\n2.  **AI Solutions & Infrastructure (Subscription & Licensing):**\n    *   **Subscriptions:** Revenue from premium subscriptions on **X and Grok**, recognized ratably over the subscription term (month-to-month to one year).\n    *   **Data Licensing:** Revenue from data licensing arrangements, recognized ratably as the customer consumes the data (terms from month-to-month to two years).\n    *   **API Access:** Revenue from providing API access to Grok models, recognized ratably over the contract term or as services are consumed for usage-based arrangements.\n\n**Key Trend:** The segment's revenue growth is increasingly driven by **X and Grok subscriptions** and **data licensing**, while historically, substantially all revenue in 2023-2024 came from X (formerly Twitter) through advertising, subscriptions, and licensing.\n\n### **Key Performance Indicators (KPIs) & Metrics**\n| Metric | 2026 Q1 | 2025 FY | 2024 FY | 2023 FY | Trend & Note |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| **Nameplate Compute Draw (GW)** | 1 | 0.8 | 0.3 | 0 | **Rapidly Scaling.** Measures installed compute power capacity. |\n| **Segment Revenue** | $818M | $3,201M | $2,620M | $2,961M | 2025 saw 22% growth; 2024 saw an 11.5% decline from 2023 due to ad losses. |\n| **Segment Loss from Operations** | $(2,469)M | $(6,355)M | $(1,561)M | $(3,973)M | **Significant Losses.** Reflects heavy investment phase. |\n| **Segment Adjusted EBITDA** | $(609)M | $(1,237)M | $347M | $1,222M | Turned negative in 2025 as investment scaled. |\n\n### **Cost Structure & Investment Focus**\n*   **Cost of Revenue:** Includes infrastructure costs (data center leases, energy, depreciation of servers), revenue share expenses, payment processor fees, creator payments, amortization of intangibles, and allocated labor. Expected to increase in absolute dollars but decrease as a percentage of revenue with monetization.\n*   **Research & Development (R&D):** Mainly relates to **training Grok**, developing next-gen AI products, and associated data center costs. This is a major and rapidly growing expense line:\n    *   **2025 AI Segment R&D:** Included $3.89B increase driven by **GPU hardware depreciation** and cloud/data center costs for expansions.\n    *   **2026 Q1 AI Segment R&D:** Included $1.47B increase for similar reasons.\n*   **Capital Expenditures:** Massive and scaling quickly to deploy power and compute.\n    *   **2026 Q1 AI CapEx:** **$7,723 million**.\n    *   **2025 AI CapEx:** **$5,633 million**.\n    *   **2024 AI CapEx:** $463 million.\n\n### **Forward-Looking Information & Strategy**\n*   **Investment Horizon:** The company expects a **multi-year investment period** before these deployments translate into sustained positive AI Segment Adjusted EBITDA.\n*   **Market Opportunity:** Investments aim to capture a **$26.5 trillion potential market opportunity** for AI.\n*   **Financing:** Plans to access a range of **debt and equity financing solutions** as a public company to fund growth and maintain liquidity.\n*   **Infrastructure Priority:** The company will prioritize growth and investment in AI applications and compute infrastructure. It expects to allocate significant **future launch capacity** from its Space segment to the AI segment.\n*   **Revenue Recognition & Judgments:** For complex contracts (like Starshield), the company must use significant management judgment to estimate total costs and progress toward completion, with changes recognized in the current period.\n\n**In summary, the AI segment (xAI) is in a phase of aggressive, infrastructure-heavy investment to build a vertically integrated platform for next-generation AI and a path to AGI. Its revenue is transitioning from legacy X advertising toward Grok and AI infrastructure services, but it is currently operating at a significant loss due to the enormous scale of compute investment required, which management views as essential for long-term market capture.**",
